&lt;p&gt;Full time Band 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Lead Paediatric Diabetic Nurse Specialist to join and lead our established children’s diabetes nursing team. We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated nurse to join a committed multidisciplinary paediatric diabetes team. This is a challenging, fulfilling and exciting post .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our multidisciplinary diabetes team provides a service for children and young people aged 0-19 years. The post holder will be a key member of the multidisciplinary team who lead and deliver a specialist clinical service for children and young people living with diabetes, as set out in the Paediatric Diabetes Best Practice Tariff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant would be leading and coordinating the care for children and young people with diabetes and their families in a variety of settings including: hospital, home and school. They would be providing essential assessment, ongoing care and support as well as creating and delivering educational programs, both for children and young people and their families and member of ASPH and the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;With close support from the multidisciplinary team: Specialist Dietician, Psychologist and a number of Paediatric Consultants, the post holder will have the opportunity to build upon their existing knowledge and skills, and further develop their own nursing practice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
